Executable
Class Publisher

java.lang.Object
  Executable.Publisher
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable
public class Publisher
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable

This class make possible the administration of Online and Offline information, here we can decide which kind of status display and where write it. The general status (Corba, Acs, Alma, Subsystems and opserver) is written on cacheFile located on $AXIS2_HOME/WebOMCFiles, if this file not exist, using WebOMCLauncher.createFile we can create this file, but, if $AXIS2_HOME not exist or WebOMCFiles directory not exist, then the program will fail. This program is a runnable so, on the run implementation, we decide when write the status on the files and wait some time specified on the constructor, with a refresh parameter.

Publisher

public Publisher(java.lang.String _managerLoc,
                 java.lang.String _clientName,
                 java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,Archivo> _files,
                 java.lang.Long _refresh,
                 java.lang.String[] antennas,
                 java.lang.String[] devices,
                 java.lang.String _brokerURI)
          throws java.lang.Exception
This is the constructor of Publisher class, here will try to connect with manager, because we try to create an Acs Client, if the connection was not possible, then will throw and exception saying that its impossible to get conection, then WebOMCLauncher will put a message on a file, and will try again.

Parameters:
_managerLoc - Indicate the location of manager calculated by WebOMCLauncher.
_clientName - Indicate the name with will register on the ACSLogger.
_files - Indicate the hashmap of files where will be written the status information.
_refresh - Indicate the tame between updates
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - Indicate that was unnable to create a client, contain the message to be written on the corresponding file.
